did.abstract: This collection consists of material relating to the United Brewery Workers Union. Included are historical material, convention proceedings, General Executive Board minutes and general correspondence microfilm, and newspapers. These range in date from 1888-1977.
did.physloc: Materials are stored off-site, and will require additional retrieval time. Please contact the Special Collections Research Center for more information.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into six series: Historical Materials, Convention Materials, General Executive Board Session Materials, General Correspondence Microfilm, The Brewery Worker newspaper and materials relating to Local 222.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The United Brewery Workers Records consists of convention proceedings, Officers' and Presidents' reports, General Executive Board minutes, miscellaneous printed matter and general correspondence microfilm. The materials range in date from 1888-1977.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: In 1973, after many years of sometimes violent jurisdictional disputes with the International Brotherhood of Teamsters (IBT), the International Union of United Brewery, Flour, Cereal, Soft Drink and Distillery Workers of America merged with its arch-rival, becoming the Brewery and Soft Drink Conference of the IBT. Founded in 1886 as the National Union of Brewery Workmen, the union was largely composed of German immigrants. Its convention proceedings and publications were printed in German until 1903 and bilingually until 1917.

Affiliated with the American Federation of Labor (AFL) from the time of its founding, the United Brewery Workers Union withdrew from the AFL in 1946 to affiliate with the Congress of Industrial Organizations (CIO). A particularly violent series of jurisdictional battles between the United Brewery Workers and the Teamsters took place in Pittsburgh in 1946 which included strikes, picket lines, street fights and lawsuits. What became known as the "Pittsburgh Beer War" was the subject of a Congressional investigation in 1947.

The decision to merge with the Teamsters stemmed from the closing of hundreds of local breweries in the 1950s and 1960s as well as the expanded competition with large national brewers such as Anheuser-Busch. Due to the numerous name changes the union undertook over the years and to the length of its name at the time of the merger, the collection is referred to as The United Brewery Workers Records.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Please cite unpublished materials in the following way:
Please provide the title and date of item, catalog number (if applicable it will be found written on the folder), name of the collection, name of the repository, and location of the repository.

scopecontent.p: This series consists of historic material relating to the United Brewery Workers. These range in date from 1917-1960. Included is the Brewery Worker's Constitution and legal documents.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of material relating to the United Brewery Workers annual conventions dating from 1888-1973. Included are official proceedings, minutes and President and Officer's reports.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into three subseries: Official proceedings, Minutes, and President and Officer's reports.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains offical proceedings of the United Brewery Workers conventions dating from 1888-1973. Material covered within these proceedings include lists of delegates, session activities, orders and resolutions, auditing committee statistics and rules of order.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries comprises of stenotyped records of the United Brewery Workers conventions dating from 1952-1971. They contain detailed descriptions of the the events of the conventions, announcements and reports by the Constitution Committee and the Resolutions Committee.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries, dating from 1917-1971, contains the President's and Officer's reports presented at the United Brewery Workers conventions. Issues covered within the reports include reviews of events, statistics and graphs of sales production, information on strikes, selling trends and average wages.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into two subseries: Minutes and Session mailers.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of material relating to the United Brewery Workers General Executive Board sessions dating from 1947-1977. Included are session minutes and mailers.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The material in this subseries contains the recorded minutes of the General Executive Board sessions dating from 1935-1970. The minutes detail the proceedings of the sessions including information regarding reports given, contracts endorsed and elections held.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains mailers and proofs of the sessions of the General Executive Board dating from 1941-1947. These records chornicle the events of the General Executive Board sessions and were mailed to members of the United Brewery Workers union.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of material relating to the United Brewery Workers general correspondence in microfilm form. The reels range in date from 1911-1947. Most, however, are from the 1930s and 1940s. Many Local Unions have more than one reel concerning their undertakings.
